|Example.Language=Russian
|Example.Text=Американцы должны молчать, а не мычать. Почему они засадили Ассанжа в тюрьму? Есть русская пословица "Чья бы корова мычала, а твоя бы молчала"
|Example.Gloss=Americans should be silent and not moo. Why did they send Assange to jail? Is it democracy? There is a Russian proverb “Whatever cow moos, it shouldn’t be yours”
|Example.English translation=Americans should be silent and not moo. Why did they send Assange to jail? Is it democracy? There is a Russian proverb “Who's talking, and your silence would”.
|Example.Provenance=Putin's speech
|Example.Comments=about Americans criticizing Russian democracy while commenting on persecution of Julian Assange - WikiLeaks. The meaning of the proverb - one shouldn't criticize or blame others for doing smth, if one does the same.
